running around lately.

321
00:18:16,611 --> 00:18:18,178
I don't know why
they should scare me.

322
00:18:18,211 --> 00:18:19,644
I don't believe in ghosts.

323
00:18:19,678 --> 00:18:26,611
But still-- All that stuff
gives me the creeps anyway.

324
00:18:30,144 --> 00:18:31,444
[making siren sounds]

325
00:18:31,478 --> 00:18:32,378
-Huh?

326
00:18:32,411 --> 00:18:34,011
Here comes that
dude who's always

327
00:18:34,044 --> 00:18:35,811
fighting monsters on the street.

328
00:18:35,844 --> 00:18:38,044
[making siren sounds]

329
00:18:38,078 --> 00:18:40,311
-How you doing Fro-man?

330
00:18:40,344 --> 00:18:41,144
-Huh?

331
00:18:41,178 --> 00:18:42,478
-You filming a scene tonight?

332
00:18:42,511 --> 00:18:45,478
[laughter] I think I just
gave you a new nickname, bro.

333
00:18:45,511 --> 00:18:47,011
-Shut up, you idiot.

334
00:18:47,044 --> 00:18:49,044
there's no time for
your stupid jokes.

335
00:18:49,078 --> 00:18:50,978
You better listen to
me, was listen good.

336
00:18:51,011 --> 00:18:54,244
If you stay here, your life
expectancy is going to be zero.

337
00:18:54,278 --> 00:18:57,744
[making siren sounds]

338
00:18:57,778 --> 00:18:58,411
-Wow.

339
00:18:58,444 --> 00:18:59,744
What's up with him?

340
00:18:59,778 --> 00:19:01,111
What a jerk!

341
00:19:01,144 --> 00:19:04,711
All I was trying to
do was say hello.

342
00:19:04,744 --> 00:19:06,378
Now that I stop
to think about it,

343
00:19:06,411 --> 00:19:08,244
I've never seen
this guy's TV show.

344
00:19:08,278 --> 00:19:10,444
Maybe it's on cable.

345
00:19:10,478 --> 00:19:14,344
I wonder if it's any good.

346
00:19:14,378 --> 00:19:14,811
Huh?

347
00:19:18,744 --> 00:19:24,478
[panicked gasping]

348
00:19:24,511 --> 00:19:26,211
-No way!

349
00:19:26,244 --> 00:19:27,278
I don't believe in ghosts.

350
00:19:27,311 --> 00:19:28,378
I don't believe in ghosts.

351
00:19:28,411 --> 00:19:32,211
I don't believe in ghosts!

352
00:19:32,244 --> 00:19:34,544
[screaming]

353
00:19:34,578 --> 00:19:36,544
[stuttering] Wait a minute.

354
00:19:36,578 --> 00:19:39,178
You're that guys I saw in
our school earlier today.

355
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:40,511
What are you doing here?

356
00:19:40,544 --> 00:19:43,011
And even more importantly,
why are you covered in blood?

357
00:19:43,044 --> 00:19:45,311
And what's with the sword?

358
00:19:45,344 --> 00:19:46,278
-Hm?

359
00:19:46,311 --> 00:19:49,244
You're that boy
from this afternoon.

360
00:19:49,278 --> 00:19:52,311
[grunt]

361
00:19:52,344 --> 00:19:53,978
[laughter]

362
00:19:54,011 --> 00:19:55,511
-What's the matter Soul Reaper?

363
00:19:55,544 --> 00:19:58,911
If that's the best you've
got, you'd better give up now.

364
00:19:58,944 --> 00:20:00,044
Hah!

365
00:20:00,078 --> 00:20:01,911
-I knew shouldn't have
come out here tonight.

366
00:20:01,944 --> 00:20:03,778
I just wanted to get some juice.

367
00:20:03,811 --> 00:20:06,444
Now guys are talking
about Soul Reapers.

368
00:20:06,478 --> 00:20:08,478
Wait-- maybe they want mine!

369
00:20:08,511 --> 00:20:09,978
-Hey, kid.

370
00:20:10,011 --> 00:20:12,944
[panicked moaning]

371
00:20:12,978 --> 00:20:15,744
-I've got a proposition
I want to talk about.

372
00:20:15,778 --> 00:20:17,411
You want to hear it?

373
00:20:17,444 --> 00:20:20,944
-Well, now that all depends
on what you have to say.

374
00:20:20,978 --> 00:20:22,044
Is there blood involved?

375
00:20:22,078 --> 00:20:23,978
-We're looking for a
place to stay tonight,

376
00:20:24,011 --> 00:20:25,978
and we don't have
much cash on us.

377
00:20:26,011 --> 00:20:27,644
You have a place I imagine.

378
00:20:27,678 --> 00:20:29,011
But you've stumbled
into a battle

379
00:20:29,044 --> 00:20:30,911
and you're about to get killed.

380
00:20:30,944 --> 00:20:33,211
-Actually, it
appears that you may

381
00:20:33,244 --> 00:20:34,811
be the one who's
about to get killed.

382
00:20:34,844 --> 00:20:36,678
-I haven't finished yet!

383
00:20:36,711 --> 00:20:39,844
Here's the deal-- you put us
up at your place for a while.

384
00:20:39,878 --> 00:20:43,911
And in return for that, I'll
protect you from these bozos.

385
00:20:43,944 --> 00:20:45,278
-Huh?

386
00:20:45,311 --> 00:20:47,211
-Are you brain-damaged
or something?!

387
00:20:47,244 --> 00:20:48,378
It's a simple question!

388
00:20:48,411 --> 00:20:50,078
Give me a yes or no!

389
00:20:50,111 --> 00:20:50,644
-Yes!

390
00:20:50,678 --> 00:20:51,511
You can stay!

391
00:20:54,311 --> 00:20:55,311
-All right.

392
00:20:55,344 --> 00:20:57,511
Thanks for the invite.

393
00:20:57,544 --> 00:20:58,444
Hey, you.

394
00:20:58,478 --> 00:20:59,811
-Hm?

395
00:20:59,844 --> 00:21:03,211
-You were so busy trying to kill
me I didn't catch your name.

396
00:21:03,244 --> 00:21:03,911
-Oh.

397
00:21:03,944 --> 00:21:05,478
I guess you're right.

398
00:21:05,511 --> 00:21:07,044
I'm Arrancar 13.

399
00:21:07,078 --> 00:21:10,244
Also known-- Hm.

400
00:21:10,278 --> 00:21:11,844
-Hm?

401
00:21:11,878 --> 00:21:12,911
-Never mind.

402
00:21:12,944 --> 00:21:14,278
Waste of time.

403
00:21:14,311 --> 00:21:16,511
I just realized there's
no point in giving out

404
00:21:16,544 --> 00:21:19,178
my name to somebody
I'm about to kill.

405
00:21:19,211 --> 00:21:21,044
Heh.

406
00:21:21,078 --> 00:21:22,944
-Is that right.

407
00:21:22,978 --> 00:21:26,278
It seems that you and I operate
with very different rules

408
00:21:26,311 --> 00:21:28,244
of etiquette.

409
00:21:28,278 --> 00:21:29,711
-Huh?

410
00:21:29,744 --> 00:21:32,278
-Maybe it's in fact
that you're part Hollow.

411
00:21:32,311 --> 00:21:35,478
But we let our opponents know
the name of their killers.

412
00:21:35,511 --> 00:21:38,411
It's something I teach
every pupil I train.

413
00:21:38,444 --> 00:21:40,378
If you're prepared
to die in battle,

414
00:21:40,411 --> 00:21:42,111
you should want to
die knowing name

415
00:21:42,144 --> 00:21:44,511
of the person who defeated you.

416
00:21:44,544 --> 00:21:46,978
So allow me to introduce myself.

417
00:21:51,144 --> 00:21:55,344
I'm Ikkaku Madarame, third
seat of the Zaraki squad.

418
00:21:55,378 --> 00:21:57,178
I won't bother
spelling it for you.

419
00:21:57,211 --> 00:22:01,744
I doubt your brain can
absorb that much information.

420
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:05,211
Just know that I'm the one
who's about to kill you!

421
00:23:47,420 --> 00:23:49,353
Did you know an
Arrancar's tough skin

422
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:51,053
is written as "steel
hide" in kanji,

423
00:23:51,086 --> 00:23:52,786
but is actually
pronounced as "iron"?

424
00:23:52,820 --> 00:23:54,520
HITSUGAYA: Sometimes
I wonder if your skin

425
00:23:54,553 --> 00:23:55,886
is even tougher than theirs.

426
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:59,086
Oh please, don't compare my
soft complexion to those beasts.

427
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:01,420
HITSUGAYA: Tough skin isn't
always found on the surface.

428
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:15,086
-The Soul Reapers.

429
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,486
-That's the latest
information we

430
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:19,820
have from the world
of the living, ma'am.

431
00:24:19,853 --> 00:24:22,586
-Continue to keep watch over
them and report back to me.

432
00:24:22,620 --> 00:24:23,553
-Yes, ma'am.

433
00:24:23,586 --> 00:24:25,553
Here are the
surveillance photos.

434
00:24:25,586 --> 00:24:26,053
-Very well.

435
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:39,353
-Oh wow, Lady Yoroichi, you're
such an impressive woman.

436
00:24:39,386 --> 00:24:40,353
What style.

437
00:24:40,386 --> 00:24:43,320
You even look
amazing when you eat.

